A GOOD METHOD OF DESTROYING RATS AND MICE.

Every time you bring grain into your barn, you must, in putting down the
three first sheaves, repeat the following words: "Rats and mice, these
three sheaves I give to you, in order that you may not destroy any of my
wheat." The name of the kind of grain must also be mentioned.

